title: For Sale/Trade:  Saiga AK Slidefire stock & mags.
postcontent: I have a Slidefire (SSAI-MCXAE) stock made for unconverted Saiga rifles/shotguns. I bought it for my Saiga .308, but since it has a different style trigger than all the other calibers (of course, ugh!) it won’t work for me. Also selling a few magazines for a 7.62x39 Saiga. These particular magazines started out as regular AK mags, but were modified to work in a Saiga without installing a bullet guide. Metal was welded in over the front locking tab, to recreate a built-in bullet guide, which prevents the rounds from slamming into the side of the chamber—which is what would happen if you used standard AK mags in an out-of-the-box Saiga. The AK/Saiga mags still lock in a regular AK, but unsure if they would still function or not—though it appears they would, I cannot guarantee it. I do however guarantee the mags to function flawlessly in unconverted Saiga’s. As you probably have heard a dozen times, it is very likely (especially with bipartisan support) that these stocks will be banned shortly. These have been banned from sales, or are out of stock everywhere online.....get them while you still can!!asking $550 for the stock and magazines, and will certainly consider trades of equal or better value.
